item.title: Underwater Hockey comes 3rd at Nationals
item.author: Shut W Leung,
item.description: Imperial’s Underwater Hockey team won their first ever medal at the University Nationals tournament on Saturday 8th March in Plymouth, finishing 3rd out of 17 teams. A team of 9 players went to Plymouth Life Centre (the home of Tom Daley) over the weekend as part of the biggest students’ underwater …
